{"name":"Ronin","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.wwPbqokiVfN7nC3P"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Ronin</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;Nothing worth having is easily attained&hellip; Sometimes you must fight for what is yours&hellip; and what you believe in. Until they get to know the real you, people&rsquo;s stereotypes don&rsquo;t mean much. I came here to live free, not die for money.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Jack, Old World Ronin</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The term Ronin refers to samurai who, as a result of either losses in battle, the untimely death of their lord or master, or their own misdeeds, have been dispossessed of their fief and their noble sponsorship. Under normal circumstances, samurai who would dishonor themselves are conditioned to commit seppuku&mdash;a ritualistic form of suicide meant to preserve the samurai&rsquo;s honor in death, but this is not always the case. In these tumultuous times their numbers have increased rapidly; they remained a great cause of disorder throughout the land of Nippon and Cathay, becoming mercenaries, guards, bandits and crime lords. They are no less deadly in combat than their noble brethren the Samurai, but their freedom from many of the rules and regulations binding them to their duties from both the Bushido Code and their lords makes them significantly more dangerous to cross. While samurai are certainly capable of their own cruelties and enforce unfair laws against the common people, the Ronin are considered honor-less and need not hold themselves to the same standard.</p>\n<p>In the late-25th century IC many impoverished samurai were attracted to the employment of Western foreigners from the country of Westerland as a chance to restore some of their lost wealth and status. Large numbers of Ronin dissatisfied with their current treatment, or out of boredom, left for these foreign lands spreading to parts of the Empire, Bretonnia, Estalia and Tilea searching for work in various fields. The vast majority end up taking criminal work in some form or another; banditry is common, as is becoming gang enforcers and utilizing their years of training and discipline to climb through the ranks and start their own criminal empires. Those that follow this path are referred to as Yakuza and are the bane of law enforcement.</p>\n<p>Not all Ronin are so ruthless. While many suffer great misfortune, it isn&rsquo;t uncommon for them to perform great acts of kindness. Adventuring and exploration are in their blood as much as any other nomadic warrior of their kind, and tales of bands of Ronin fighting off Greenskin, Beastmen and bandit incursions to protect villages and innocent lives are just as common as their tales of brutality and ruthlessness. In recent years tales have sprung around the Empire and beyond of men and women in strange robes entering towns clearing them of criminals, invaders and hidden chaos cultists asking for nothing more than a cup of tea and a night&rsquo;s rest. The most famous is a man who goes by the name of &ldquo;Jack&rdquo;, a Ronin dressed in white and grey foreign robes, wearing a straw hat; he is said to have slaughtered Beast Lords, Orc Bosses and Skaven Warlords in single combat across Estalia, Tilea and the Empire. He asks for little if anything in return. Despite no one knowing his true name, when a Tilean noble of Miragliano asked him for anything he desired after preventing a Skaven invasion from besetting the city the Ronin merely asked he be given a new name befitting of a local commoner. The people of Miragliano voted and the title of &ldquo;Jack&rdquo; was granted to him for his actions in protecting the mighty principality. It is rumored many of the ratmen&rsquo;s assassins have failed in their attempts to stop Jack&rsquo;s acts of altruism.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Nipponese)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Rogue</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Ronin Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.W4bDjEIVzVFsH9C2]{Nomad}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Xk5tp3aasPNtk4zt]{Stealth (Rural)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IFKWu98qmWpaSfUi]{Ambidextrous}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zImcTgEl2XNnbu5W]{Hardy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jack, Katana, Straw Hat</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.bLxZJk7ci0T28lzg]{Ronin}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.X16IoUlKcVLI4MRw]{Language (Wastelander)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.SHH2vUpNxj0wmmPT]{Well-prepared}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Backpack, Tent, Wooden Training Katanas</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.QTRGiD6fk2MCsxEg]{Gokudō}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Etiquette)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.gO9QSxBmZkpLNNcv]{Lightning Strike}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Cooking Set, Melee Weapon (Any)</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.cIWYg3yFFWj6apeA]{Master Ronin}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Politics)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.NDetl9BhAQBVnHKf]{Combat Master}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.RbnrfHf7GSQap0ig]{Kingpin}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.QolNfSUkezLoAcky]{Reversal}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Clothing and Hat</p>","_id":"51449PY9Sz9whiSO"}
{"name":"Zunu","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ZpaMIqo1srxXCI8m"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Zunu</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;I need no bodyguard at all, for even the bravest creatures who approach me get weak at the knees and their hearts turn to water, whilst their heads become giddy and incapable of thinking as the sweat of fear paralyses them.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Impi Shuku, Skaven Btucher and Defender of Teotiqua</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Southlands are a land dominated by the trading empires of Araby, Cathay and the High Elves, with the Lizardmen Kingdoms being the leading military might that battles endlessly against the frequent swarms of Undead, Greenskins, Skaven and Chaos. However, the native human Southlanders are no slouch when it comes to fighting, their Zunu warriors being amongst the fiercest combatants on foot able to chase down their prey with lightning speed for days.</p>\n<p>The organization of the Zunu armies are profoundly different to their professional Empire counterpart, a part-time citizen militia, the means by which a nation of herdsmen come together periodically in national service. At the heart of the system are guilds. These guilds are a means of exercising central control over the most productive element in the group&ndash;its young men and women&ndash;and prior to the emergence of the Southlands Kingdoms thousands of years ago, each chiefdom raised its own guilds.</p>\n<p>Every two or three years, young warriors who reach their late teens are called and gathered together at the royal homestead and form into a unit. They are given a regimental name, told to wear a specific uniform of feathers and furs on ceremonial occasions, with older veterans appointed as officers over them. These units then serve as the chiefdom&rsquo;s labor gang, police force, hunting-parties, and army. Although housed in special settlements while assembled, there is no infrastructure to support them for extended periods, and it is usual for them to disperse and return to their homes when they had performed their appointed tasks.</p>\n<p>Zunu armies are mobilized quickly whenever invading forces come into notice. With the recent rise of the Southland Kings thanks to good relations with the Lizardmen, individual chiefdoms within the Southland Kingdoms have ceased to raise their own guilds, and the right to do so has become the prerogative of the kings. The guilds by 2500 IC number in the hundreds or even thousands of men apiece and are quartered when mustering in their large royal homesteads. A robust military ethic prevails amongst them, jealousy of their honors and distinctions being prevalent, with scuffles between guilds now common.</p>\n<p>Uniformed war-shields were traditionally made using animal hide with weapons brought by the warrior. The long-bladed, thick hafted stabbing spear has remained the favorite for thousands of years. However, by the 2300&rsquo;s IC, due to bettering relations with the Lizardmen, seeing Southlanders as allies as ordained by The Great Plan, Zunu warriors are being increasingly equipped with Obsinite shields, spears, maces and blades forged by Skink Artisan-Priests. Some Zunu have even had the honor of fighting alongside the towering Saurus of the Lizardmen against the innumerable threats of the Southlands, with the most seasoned and battle-hardened receiving gifts and magical trinkets for their service. Some Southlanders even managed to learn and understand the Lizardmen Language of Saurian despite it being unpronounceable to other species.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Southlanders)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Witch Doktor Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.qPNg1T3gxuPbWddQ]{Militiaman}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-c