{"name":"Desert Rider","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.M8eUQ1pvzKudLmgd"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Desert Rider</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;By the Lady, those heathens of the sands know no honor! No glory! They pillage us at night and steal from which they cannot kill. So long as I live, I shall hunt down and vanquish those so called &lsquo;Demons of the Desert&rsquo; until there is not but sand and blood!&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Sir Jean-Luc Girault, Bretonnian Crusader</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;We never had a chance sir. They came out of nowhere. Before we could turn they were in among us, shouting their chilling battle-cries as they cut us down. It's true we ran from them sir, but these were not men - they were demons on horseback.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">- The Mercenary Gunter Frieshiem, explaining his part in the infamous Rout of Rifraffa</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The deserts of Araby are a hostile and unforgiving land, rife with Greenskins and undead. The sun scorched dunes burn with a heat high enough to cook a man to death in a few hours, and water is more precious than gold. Under these conditions it takes a hardy group of people to live in such a harsh environment. These nomads make up the bulk of much of the cavalry at the sultan&rsquo;s command. Hardy and zealous as any priest of Ormazd, these individuals charge across the dunes ambushing, butchering and enslaving their foes with ruthless efficiency. Much like the corsairs of Lashiek, these Desert Riders come from many walks of life: nobles, commoners, peasants and more make up the ranks of the Desert Riders with the nomads and bandits outside the cities making up the vast majority. They also hold a large stake in the Arab slave trade, ambushing and enslaving many travelers, native or foreign, and defending the borders between the Land of the Dead and Araby.</p>\n<p>Desert Riders make up the majority of the light cavalry for Araby with many being taken in to serve in the name of the various caliphs, sheikhs and viziers that rule its cities and territories. While some serve out of a sense of duty, pride or for religious reasonings, the vast majority are simply paid into service. They fight using the terrain to their advantage, able to engage invading forces on their terms with day or night ambushes--hails of arrows peppering their enemies, allowing the rest of their forces to close in and cut down the trespassers. Many Tomb King attempts at conquest and Greenskin warbands have ended at the hands of these brave individuals. Day and night, these experts of the desert sands of Araby are the main shield against the many evils that plague their people. The most famous being the Desert Dogs lead by Al-Muktar, an Old Worlder turned mercenary king after winning over the loyalty of a powerful band of Desert Riders who had initially captured him. Since then he has carved out a reputation as one of the most powerful mercenary leaders in Araby, if not all of history.</p>\n<p>Not all Desert Riders are slavers, bandits and cavalrymen, however. Many seek fortune, travelling across the sands and exploring the ancient tombs and ruined cities of millennia&rsquo;s past. Bel-Aliad, being the most sought after, is the place where most young and ambitious adventurers go to seek their fortune--and many their doom. Its ancient halls and sunken homes are said to hide untold treasures, attracting many to its domain. Desert Riders who enter and live to tell the tail are said to come out with powerful magical artifacts, including swords surrounded by flames, jeweled rings that grant the wearer divine luck and lamps that are rumored to hold the mystical Djinn trapped within them that sell for a fortune to the right magician.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Arabyan)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Rogue</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Desert Rider Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.9jVRfSbAERQpspa9]{Pillager}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.iYan4z52v7HYM9u9]{Drive}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Uxnxmtvshz8OAVaX]{Language (Thieves Tongue)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Araby)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}&nbsp;<em>or </em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bBLK2hznjPlby6Jb]{Play (Drums)} <em>or </em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bBLK2hznjPlby6Jb]{Play (Flute)}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.MeXCAQ3wqJzX07X7]{Ride (Camel)} or @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}</em><br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.BbStIySkF1hDM2zq]{Lightning Reflexes}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.5lcttqGToT54WFrl]{Marksman}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.9CAkY3SQjQxRTlNJ]{Roughrider}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.1dUizIgLBgn4jICC]{Strider (Desert)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Riding Horse (Arabyan Pureblood with Fast Trait) or Riding Camel with Saddle and Tack, d10 Rations</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.Aswr9SHNL9zY8FX5]{Desert Rider}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.ZQSm2AwrgT2cHG0C]{Ranged (Bow)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rvd0S8Z0v2m0MHmD]{Sleight of Hand}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.XIcDsaW4D8wScezw]{Accurate Shot}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Yiw5h1Kj4B2WLlfm]{Cardsharp}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.jLJzZb4keVvE0qRv]{Deadeye Shot}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.x0WMGwuQzReXcQrs]{Night Vision}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Map, Recurve Bow and 10 Arrows, Tent</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.jxuEaeZFn955CrwD]{Desert Raider}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Undead)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Xk5tp3aasPNtk4zt]{Stealth (Rural)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rt2rGSwFDCDHPh0A]{Track}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.tXKX29QZBdHmyMc7]{Combat Reflexes}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.FjTnaxixsu1ShNNr]{Trick Riding}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Tent and Carpet, Scimitar</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.OWzVpaVH3mWdrIQc]{Demon of the Desert}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.5eDd6iFeR9G6cCfz]{Fast Shot}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Desert Garb, Unit of Desert Riders</p>","_id":"833K3OihZ1ObdKro"}
{"name":"Swordsaint","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Hx3LZhGUeyEt62Lb"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Swordsaint</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;Know your enemy and know yourself and you can fight a hundred battles without disaster.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Shu Tsunzi, Cathayan General</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;I find the idea of our superiority often tested in my visits to this land. The skill of some of these duelists is enough to give even a Swordmaster of Hoeth some pause&hellip;\"</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Oralin the Valiant, High Elf Ambassador</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Cathay, the great empire of the far east, is the oldest human empire and among the most powerful of the human realms on the planet. Its armies are said to number from the hundreds-of-thousands to the millions, dwarfing its neighbors in raw manpower and overrunning even Greenskins in numerical supremacy. From the capital in Weijin to the heavily defended north of Cathay in Nan-Gau and southern forts bordering the tainted land of Khuresh in Xianbei, the subjects of the Celestial Dragon Emperor fight on a regular basis to defend their homeland from the tainted forces of Chaos. Skaven, Ogres, Beastmen, Greenskins and relentless invasions by the barbaric Hung tribes of the north have tested Cathay time and again for millennia, much like the Empire of man to the West. However through Cathay&rsquo;s many thousands of years of history in art, warfare and magic, they have perfected the ultimate warriors&mdash;the Swordsaints.</p>\n<p>A celestial order defined by their unwavering loyalty to the Emperor, the Swordsaints of Cathay are expert duelists of almost mythical status. Their mastery of the sword has earned them much fear and renown from both their allies and enemies. They train relentlessly, mastering techniques and styles unheard-of outside the East. With decades of practice, preparation and study put into each stroke, their combat prowess is perfected through years of aggressive fighting against the greatest of their enemies&rsquo; champions, with Chaos Warriors of the Hung, Ogre Bruisers and innumerable Greenskin Bosses being but a few examples. Masters of the art cut these foes down relentlessly over their many decades of life, with the greatest of champions granted a personal audience with the mysterious Celestial Dragon Emperor himself, gifted his blessing (not too dissimilar to The Cult of the Lady in Bretonnia) and granted a legendary Jade Longsword forged by the master smith&mdash;the Gold Wizards of Cathay.</p>\n<p>The Swordsaints are nomadic in nature, travelling the lands of Cathay and beyond and aiding the people of the land when they can. They are considered kind and approachable by the people of Cathay, as many of the more prominent Swordsaints are descendants of commoners and peasants who don&rsquo;t suffer the same dissociation with the common people unlike nobility--unusual of an order of such prestige. It is skill and not class that is sought after within its divine order, a similarity they share with the monks within the Mountains of Heaven. Many Swordsaints are remembered through shrines and statues built in their honor for their great deeds and defense of the people with each subsequent saint having a terracotta soldier made in their honor and likeness outside the Emperor&rsquo;s palace in Weijin to protect him&mdash;even in death. In Nippon, the Swordsaints are held in higher esteem among the warrior caste, as it was they who taught the samurai many of the techniques, arts and strategies they now associate with their kenjutsu and Bushido code. Those who follow the older ways of Cathay in Nippon society are known as the Kensai. In recent years, with the bridging of relations between the far East and the outsiders from Marienburg, Swordsaints have started traveling themselves abroad, to new lands not yet discovered, new cultures to explore, new people to defend and new challenges to face.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Cathayan)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Swordsaint Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.MezKHEGkxl8D7vvG]{Swordsman}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong