g>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.fdq3RFSOKl5b3WzW]{Art (Calligraphy)} <em>or&nbsp;</em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.fdq3RFSOKl5b3WzW]{Art (Poetry)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HO8vIjGTHjmenIaV]{Perform (Sword Tricks)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.NDetl9BhAQBVnHKf]{Combat Master}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.4AqSkJnFPqNuTkos]{Reaction Strike}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.x8jsChg17VQ9XgiK]{Riposte}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Bladesmith Tools</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.2BMhySAXzUBJmpKv]{Blade of the Heavens}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.hpc8g8Z9rl3fJECS]{Channelling (Azyr)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Heavens)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Audience with the Celestial Dragon Emperor, Jade Longsword</p>","_id":"8KJkgBFcMs1eOQhH"}
{"name":"Marine","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OfNCzDntmx3QWw8e"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Marine</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;Labouring hard with a shovel in the darkness, stoking a massive boiler and bathing in the heat. Life on board an Ironclad, eh? Just like being at home.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;&lsquo;One-eye&rsquo; Morgim, Sea Engineer aboard the Legend of Grimnir</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;Eataine does not field a citizen militia as all the other provinces do, instead contributing the Lothern Sea Guard to the Phoenix King's armies. Unlike the normal levy, they are not only called up in times of need, but remain at arms at all times. The riches of our people are great, and the legends greater still, so there is never any shortage of villainous cut-throats who will stoop to any depths to steal their way into our fair capital and plunder our ancestral wealth.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Recounted by Unthwe Windrider, Herald of the Phoenix King</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Marines are ship-borne soldiers who can be found in the Imperial fleet and onboard the larger private vessels. Marines protect their ships from pirates, Norse marauders, and other raiders. Unlike seamen, whose primary duty is sailing the ship, Marines are onboard only to fight. When in port, Marines frequently form press gangs to fill out the ship&rsquo;s crew. More than one unsuspecting citizen has awoken at sea after taking a belaying pin to the head from an overzealous press ganger. Due to these activities, and their own drunken brawling, Marines are resented in many seaside communities. When raiders attack, however, these same citizens are quick to accept the aid of battle-hardened Marines.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p>Despite their reputation within the Empire as part soldier and part thug, the word &ldquo;Marine&rdquo; is used as a description for any kind of maritime combatant. Within the lands of Ulthuan, the High Elves house and train powerful maritime warriors known as the Lothern Seaguard, masters of ship-to-ship combat and renown marksman. The Dwarfs of Barak-Varr house the largest fleet within the Dwarfen realms and field powerful sea-savvy warriors to fend off the endless tide of Greenskins from the Badlands and aid in sending ironclad warships to fend off Norscan invaders across the Sea of Claws. Even amongst the Empire there are distinguished regiments of Marines who do not fit the typical stereotype often associated with their rough reputation. The armies of Ostland and Nordland maintain powerful fleets armed with highly trained and respected marine corps, such as the Nordland Seahawks. So, while the typical marine is often visualized as a brutish, war-torn human sailor prone to shady dealings and drunken barfights, the requirements for what truly categorizes a marine is broad enough to encompass a much wider range of brave men and women across the Old World.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human,Dwarf, Gnome, Halfling, High Elf</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Riverfolk</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Marine Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.xRraZqLU0VGZ8MSw]{Sailor Recruit}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.KL4pCOqma5E7fLG4]{Row}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.9s8S1BlR4cd5UeN8]{Sail (Frigate)} or @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.n8IfmLt4kzMhIKIv]{Sail (Patrol Boat)}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.hodHqFNKAmu40ajh]{Swim}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.cAxNctMFWIAjDgV3]{Diceman}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Zf0vk2rjllpDh0Ua]{Very Strong}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Bucket, Brush, Mop, Hand Weapon, Uniform</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.P7g6fYKa9oy68wjf]{Marine}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.UFunAopCNaD8Zdc7]{Entertain (Singing)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Z9hQe46ykQBZneoU]{Ranged (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.2Nzqsc9aclP6rpnl]{Dirty Fighting}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.J9MK0AIaTbvd5oF6]{Drilled}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Ij9N3G8jzxb4lrwy]{Sea Legs}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IT3s7rmQFGNzIfYq]{Shieldsman}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jack, Weapon (Any)</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.YfaV680zIqFNVXcE]{Petty Officer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.qy68sCupAbzhlvVU]{Trade (Carpenter)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Guilders)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.L74MT9BDwE4CfutY]{Old Salt}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.8oWhzlcw7oiHGMFu]{Unshakable}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Officer&rsquo;s Quarters, Symbol of Rank, Unit of Sailors</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.wqscOI8MLbJpXwFy]{Marine Captain}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.afREA9q7v4Scuozn]{Orientation}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.WEH97InIX29nzgW1]{Pilot}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Letter of Commission, Map, Orders, Quality Uniform, Sextant, Spyglass, Warship and Crew</p>","_id":"CKFWLGbxURlhDPTI"}
{"name":"Vimto Monk","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pkdYUJhqZmeHMmn3"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Vimto Monk</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;There is no fear for one whose mind is not filled with desire. You must work out your own salvation and not depend on others, lest be taken advantage of and fall down the path to Chaos.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Noyamano Nobuo, High Priest of the Cult of Simca</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;Up! Up into man-thing nest! Up to their streets and their cellars! Up to their granaries and their stockyards! Up to their homes and their temples! They kill-kill us! Revenge, yes-yes! Burn-burn the robed ones, for they-they have slain us many!&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">--Xan Speartail, Skaven Warlord</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Like many Orientals, Nipponese worship a common god called the Orange Simca, whose monks wear orange robes and spend most of their time in contemplation. Vimto is the martial version of Simcism. Nippon abounds with diverse orders of monks, either martial or clerical. The Orders select their members at a very early age and the chosen ones devote their entire lives to philosophy, theology and the martial arts. A lifetime of grueling study hones their bodies and minds to a very fine edge.&rdquo;&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</p>\n<p>Vimto monks are the warrior priests of Nippon. The naginata is the weapon most often associated with them, though many warrior monks are known to be proficient with everything from bow and arrow to tantō and wakizashi (dagger and short sword). Vimto monks, like most other warrior monks of related sects, wear robes to distinguish themselves from other soldiers and samurai, with a series of white or orange kimono-like robes in layers, one over the other, usually white underneath, and tan or saffron yellow on top. Vimto monks often fold and tie the white head cowl to cover more of their head.</p>\n<p>Finally, many warrior monks wear some form of light samurai armor, usually reinforced leather. The Vimto employ a variety of weapons. The belt of the kimono is often supplemented with a heavier sash, so a sword could be slung from it. The long tachi was probably the most common sword, though many monks may carry tantō as well. Many monks are also accomplished archers. The most traditional weapon of the monk, however, was the naginata. Their ancient enemy is that of the Skaven. Ever since clan Eshin stole the art of stealth and assassination from Nippon and Cathay they have used their abilities to kill many key members in the monk&rsquo;s priesthood. With a lack of leadership, the Skaven thought it would cause the monks to weaken and fracture, possibly fighting amongst themselves like in other religions--but it backfired miserably. The Orange Simca herself is said to have granted visions to her followers commanding them to launch an endless crusade against the Children of the Horned Rat and not to rest until they have been purged from all of Nippon forever.</p>\n<p>Their pious nature is said to grant them valuable gifts from the Orange Simca, Goddess of the Rising Sun, herself, giving them an unparalleled reputation as the living embodiment of the goddess. Seen as avatars of war, Daimyo often pay large sums of money to buy them off as mercenaries either to aid them in their campaigns of war or more commonly to avoid a conflict with them altogether. Ogres find the Vimto monks to be rather difficult competitors in the mercenary market and have launched many failed and bloody attempts to &ldquo;outbid&rdquo; their competition. Many ogre tribes in Nippon have had their contracts taken by the Vimto due to a sudden lack of &ldquo;communication&rdquo; between their employers and the ogres they initially planned to hire.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Nipponese)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Vimto Monk Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.OAeFjC3DkLkpVA1a]{Militant Priest}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.nqhgjUbJWglxU59j]{Language (Battle 