{"name":"Witch Doktor","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.jYqtkfH5MUalejXF"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Witch Doktor</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;The Witch Doktor succeeds for the same reason all the rest of us succeed, despite their barbarism. Each patient carries his or her own doktor inside him or her. They come to us doktors not knowing the truth. We are at our best when we give the doktor who resides within each patient a chance to go to work. Southlanders know this too and have mastered the art of doktoring&hellip; to the chagrin of my colleagues.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Dr. Hermann Schleiss, Professor at the Altdorf Physician&rsquo;s Guild</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Witch Doktors are the primary healers in the Southlands. They are treated as both the physical and spiritual manifestations of their gods, The Old Ones. The eldest and wisest of the Witch Doktors are powerful sages capable of healing one par with even the most seasoned Jade Wizards. It is unknown how they managed to harness such potent healing capabilities, but Imperial Scholars theorize it has something to do with the Southlanders proximity to the Lizardmen Kingdoms and the Life Slanns.</p>\n<p>Each chiefdom has its own Witch Doktors. Within the community they are treated as conduits to the gods, never to be harmed or insulted for fear of angering the spirits believed to live with them. Imperial scholars theorize this superstition came from past miscasts from lack of proper training. However, Witch Doktors start out no different than any other healer or doktor found within the Old World. They use traditional remedies and learn crude, but effective, forms of surgery, stitching up wounds and helping the poor with little to no pay for their services.</p>\n<p>Witch Doktors seemingly operate only on altruism, taking the barest minimum earning to live peacefully despite working hard to keep the chiefdom&rsquo;s citizens and warriors in top and healthy shape. It is a fascinating act of human compassion that does not go with earning the respect and admiration of the people they save. By the time they do learn how to harness the Winds of Ghyran, Witch Doktotrs have already proven themselves as capable healers without any magical intervention. Harnessing the Winds is treated as a reward&mdash;a gift from the gods themselves for their service in preserving the lives and calming the spirits of the chiefdoms they inhabit.</p>\n<p>Once they ascend, Witch Doktors are required to take on an apprentice as tradition. Not too dissimilar to the Colleges of Magic, apprentices are chosen after being magically sensed out by the more experienced magic caster. To the people of the Southlands this justifies the belief that Witch Doktors are chosen by the gods with the sages being the living conduits of their divine will.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Southlander)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Academic</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Witch Doktor Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.4ggWpIxKoYati2x0]{Medicine Man/Woman}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rvd0S8Z0v2m0MHmD]{Sleight of Hand}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.fEFAMNqh8nJIfBkM]{Field Dressing}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.u0CFf3xwiyidD9T5]{Luck}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GRRN3XAKIpEVCY7z]{Craftsman (Apothecary)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Bone Charms, Healing Draught</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.pLJERBaAQaHPK8rm]{Witch Doktor}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Herbs)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Medicine)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artifact}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.NP4EHyyh1yOLbsPU]{Surgery}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.SHH2vUpNxj0wmmPT]{Well-prepared}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quarterstaff, Trade Tools (Medicine), White Face Paint</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.j9SRJyWhuRuXPO0B]{Divine Healer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Charms)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.AcnFuDKRemLI9ey7]{Nose for Trouble}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.qdMbxW09FUoYBzmB]{Witch!}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Mortar and Pestle, Sage Robes, d10 Charms</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.HEovRMGjIJ0pRTUH]{Sage of Life}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Spirits)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLSVcLqPvnd1cg4U]{Channelling (Ghyran)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (life)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GHmXS9zGNx3PWYZc]{Master Tradesman (Apothecary)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Exotic Headdress and Feathers, Isolated Hut</p>","_id":"E2qLf5oOUxEQxPhj"}
{"name":"Dervish","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.iie9SNvPz5QoydB8"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Dervish</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;He ran at me like a devil, whirling his blades and cutting down no less than three of my brothers before reaching me. As I lifted my shield, I could not help but fear for my life, seeing those once valiant knights butchered as I coward behind them. I was driven back, blow after blow, pushing me to a wall&hellip; &lsquo;Was this the end&rsquo;, I thought? Only a moment later a knight of the Empire charging on his steed pierced through the whirling devil&rsquo;s chest with a lance. By the time the man was slain I&rsquo;d lost my companions, my pride and my honor&hellip;&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Lucas Trouv&eacute;, Crusader Knight of Bretonnia</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Dervishes of Araby are the most fanatically loyal warriors within the Cult of the Great Prophet. These whirling death-dealers represent the sheer level of piety and unquestioning faith within the Araby armies, carving a bloody path through the ranks of even the most hardened men and monsters within their sights. They are said to have no fear, no remorse and some even rumor they suffer no pain&mdash;unlikely but widely believed. They charge into battle wielding their blades and relentlessly decimate ranks of troops not dissimilar to a Dwarf Slayer or any of the many Flagellants within the Empire.</p>\n<p>Dervishes are found most often on the western portion of Araby within the Land of the Dervishes, far to the south of Lahiek and over the mountains that separate the two. They are descendants of the numerous nomadic tribes that litter the land outside the major city-states, surviving near oasis&rsquo; and making frequent pilgrimages to Martek as part of their religious traditions. Their unflinching belief in their faith has earned them renown amongst the people with some achieving such great status that they are taken in by the caliphs and viziers of Araby, and even the Sultan himself, as legendary bodyguards known as the &ldquo;Black Scimitar Guard&rdquo;&mdash;a legendary troupe first recorded to be the personal elite warriors of Sultan Jaffar, said to best many of the fiercest knights of Bretonnia and the Empire during the Great Crusade, dying to the last man and setting an example for generations to come.</p>\n<p>Dervishes are deeply nomadic as part of their tradition and are often accompanying priests of Ormazd, merchants and nobility as protection. Their fanatic loyalty to their faith and its teachings make them highly trustworthy guards once a deal has been made; plus, they ask for comparatively little to other mercenaries and escorts. They donate large portions of their income to the cult, and in recent years as trade has rapidly increased, they&rsquo;ve grown more frequent in the Empire through Marienburg attempting to convert more into their cult with very limited success.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Arabyan)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Dervish Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.6p9DZQsUKTs5lotG]{Zealot}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.d9bGxy6Y3u3rOHIN]{Lore (Theology)}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.OZMvB887CeshFy7b]{Perform (Dancing)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.oRx92ByVNEBN6YkK]{Berserk Charge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.E3vTSCzgrasNijUO]{Fleet Footed}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.hXcfygzujgyMN1uI]{Frenzy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Robes, 3 Vials of Poison</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.MZElzP57cI64jIvh]{Dervish}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.UFunAopCNaD8Zdc7]{Entertain (Singing)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Araby)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HO8vIjGTHjmenIaV]{Perform (Sword Tricks)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bVdhLdfuSAfMi3qq]{Secret Signs (Cultists)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zImcTgEl2XNnbu5W]{Hardy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.E98mVLZgE8bX5vQW]{Hatred (Heretics)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.xx8SgdWYEjKct7ym]{Implacable}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Book (Ormazd), Leather Jerkin, Religious Symbol, Scimitar</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.dU8IiJzfwnQqVuAv]{Muh&atilde;jid}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IFKWu98qmWpaSfUi]{Ambidextrous}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.BlHVzfs0Ow6IYEDw]{Furious Assault}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.AwUUEwwf2Vt4ksCN]{Sprinter}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Religious Relic</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.bKmolQWwK95TIW1G]{Black Scimitar Guard}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Speeches)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.FtjMeeGEO4YuGIBv]{Battle Rage}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-cor