.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Etiquette)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.gO9QSxBmZkpLNNcv]{Lightning Strike}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.4AqSkJnFPqNuTkos]{Reaction Strike}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Clan War Banner, Horo (Cloak), No-Dachi, Symbol of Rank and Status, Quality Courtly Garb</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.5WH4RxyxkknAtG0N]{Daimyo}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 7<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Politics)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.1IVGksL10N7GVrw3]{Noble Blood}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.x8jsChg17VQ9XgiK]{Riposte}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Land in Nippon, Large Unit of Samurai, Quality Samurai Armor and Kabuto</p>","_id":"MQICRVbJkBdrhV2Z"}
{"name":"Paymaster","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.2HTjJk3rhgpe2XPv"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Paymaster</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;It is said that money motivates neither the best people nor the best in people&rsquo;&hellip; if that is true, we may not the best people but we are absolutely the best paid&hellip;&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Leandro Cerulli, Paymaster of Braganza's Besiegers</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">\"No, they didn't look dangerous, more like a bunch of rich kids out to show off in their new armour. Very flashy they were, all gems and silk. We'll have a bit of fun, we thought. Easy pickings, we thought. Well anyone can make a mistake. Poor old captain Malvino, last mistake he ever made...\"</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Overheard in the Old Pig and Whistle, Marienburg</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The only thing that defines a mercenary company more than its reputation, fighting capability and leaders is this: Money. Without money the whole operations falls apart. The same can be said for most militaries, but whereas a Middenlander soldier is paid a wage it is reasonable to assume in a time of war most would still lay down their lives to defend their homes till their dying breathe for their honor, duty and loved ones. Not so from a mercenary company whose sole purpose is to profit off of conflict and instability. Coin is the lifeblood of any company worth its salt, and only one member has the courage, knowledge and capabilities to keep the books clean and the men paid&mdash;the Paymaster.</p>\n<p>The Paymaster guards the company&rsquo;s currency with their life&ndash;literally so because they always carry the army&rsquo;s pay chest with them. The pay chest is a heavy, iron-bound, secure-looking affair that the paymaster brings to battle on a cart, pulled by animals such as donkeys or draught horses, with the more seasoned paymasters acquiring tougher animals. Paymasters who have proven themselves to their company are often accompanied by the most elite troops as guards that ride alongside and defend the paymaster&rsquo;s chest with their lives. The cart is provided with a suitably impressive flag that also serves as the army's standard so that the troops can see exactly where the Paymaster is at all times, something they find reassuring.</p>\n<p>Paymasters come from all over the Old World and beyond but are predominantly and most highly paid within the Southern Realms. Lawyers, politicians, accountants, merchants and nobles with a spine are the predominant careers often associated with paymasters, leaving their old lives and using their expertise to make substantially more coin and quench their thirst for adventure and lusts for power. It is often touted that the most important person on the battlefield, aside from the mercenary generals themselves, are in fact the paymaster. They&rsquo;re capable combatants in their own rights, often paying the elite troops and experienced officers larger sums of coin to teach them how to fight more effectively during battle.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human, Dwarf, Gnome, Halfling, High Elf</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Courtier</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Paymaster Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ZyyGBpNUOGCRPLfq]{Bag Holder}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.iYan4z52v7HYM9u9]{Drive}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Taxes)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.34EBUkHQkrqF1sq7]{Briber}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.epPBu7x6BRWp2PHG]{Dealmaker}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Mercenaries)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.qZ4cFy6z482ZONuA]{Sturdy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Chain Shirt, Contract, 1d10 GC</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.Gv60rlAHaYDgTOwn]{Paymaster}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.nqhgjUbJWglxU59j]{Language (Battle Tongue)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Z9hQe46ykQBZneoU]{Ranged (Any)},&nbsp;<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Yiw5h1Kj4B2WLlfm]{Cardsharp}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.HIofcsDLjXGKzSZf]{Embezzle}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.AcnFuDKRemLI9ey7]{Nose for Trouble}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Bodyguards, Breastplate, Courtly Garb, Paychest and Key, 100 GC</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.SLsUSOwxN8xe8Jb9]{Company Treasurer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.b4x1qEWcevX7xK58]{Schemer}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.V9N0LMnXf1WYseCL]{Tower of Memories}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Uniform, War Wagon with Horses, 300 GC</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.mBpgdztUx41Sj8QX]{Coin King/Queen}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.oQzTJEXUx28sCiH3]{Sharp}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.OROfMcVqRnZHINkU]{Wealthy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.SHH2vUpNxj0wmmPT]{Well-prepared}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Elite Bodyguards, Quality Breastplate and Uniform, 1000 GC</p>","_id":"O2LN2owkoswx2u5a"}
{"name":"Executioner","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.JS7pm102gQJ0L7KT"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Executioner</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;May ravens alight upon you.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Morrian phrase meaning &lsquo;may your death be easy&rsquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;Never look in their eyes before you swing. In fact, don&rsquo;t even look at their face. What you do is a job, and who they are doesn&rsquo;t matter to you. Their friends, dreams, beliefs or personal history are of no concern once they have been judged to enter Morr&rsquo;s portal. When the time comes make the stroke, hit them in the back of the neck with a precise, clean strike, not just with your raw brute strength. It makes it easier to cut them down that way&hellip; and is the least painful for them.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;High Executioner Johann Schlau, lecturing an apprentice hangman for once they become a headsman</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>An executioner is an official, often within towns and cities but sometimes villages, who carries out a sentence of capital punishment on a legally condemned person.</p>\n<p>In the Empire, executioners are usually presented with an Imperial warrant authorizing or ordering them to execute sentences on behalf of the court, usually accompanying a bailiff, or magistrate in severe instances. The warrant, sealed in the symbol of Verena, protects the executioner from the charge of murder. In some Provincial militaries, the role of executioner is of grave importance as they carry out the sentences to execute known traitors within the ranks corrupted by the temptations of the Dark Gods. The common look of an executioner in the Empire is a hooded figure, sometimes clad in robes. This is done so members of criminal organizations, cultists and other unsavory individuals not fond of their comrades being beheaded do not identify and attempt retaliation on the executioner for carrying out their duty.</p>\n<p>Many executioners are professional specialists who travel a circuit or region within the Provinces of the Empire, performing their duties, because executions are in high demand in these dark times and wealthier areas are willing to pay favorable amounts of shillings for a well-trained professional. Nothing pleases a noble more than knowing for a fact their enemies are eliminated, be they cultists, criminals, rebels or even political rivals. Within their field, resident executioners also administer non-lethal physical punishments or apply torture. These torturers are highly effective at gathering information on behalf of the Imperial courts, Witch Hunters, wealthy nobles and even some criminal organizations. Their skills at maximizing pain and suffering while preventing their victim from dying outright is invaluable for anyone willing to afford them.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In the Empire, High Executioners also tax lepers and prostitutes, and control gambling houses. Their mere presence and threatening apparel are enough to test even the hardiest of citizens, and with the law on their side there is very little one can do to oppose them without going through the bureaucratic mess that is the court system. Not that it does much good, as their complaints are usually written off as a refusal to pay taxes. They are also in charge of the latrines and cesspools and disposing of animal carcasses, and many are found to be servants of Morr frequenting his temples and praying in his name before each beheading. While this is not universally the case by any means, it is theorized this worship is a method of coping as a side effect to being surrounded by death on such a regular basis.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human, Dwarf, Gnome, Halfling, High Elf</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Burgher</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Executioner Advance Scheme</h3>\n<tabl