{"_id":"QQGr71o0TDnCxLwI","name":"Druid","content":"<h1 style=\"text-align:center\">Druid</h1>\n<blockquote>“If aught must be lost, ‘twill be my honor for yours. If one must be forsaken, ‘twill be my soul for yours. Should death come anon, ‘twill be my life for yours. I am given.”<br />\n<p style=\"text-align:right\">—Senodonna, Truthsayer of Albion defending her home from Daemons during Dark Shadows</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Of all the mysteries of Albion perhaps the greatest is the purpose of the enigmatic figures known as Druids. Known as the original sorcerers by the people of Albion, when the Old ones still walked the Earth, they selected a few of the most promising of men and women and taught them many arcane secrets, with the intention that they pass these on and guide mankind to enlightenment. After the disappearance of the Old Ones they have bound chaos to the North with the Ogham stones. During the deterioration the Druids continued to remain in seclusion passing on their secrets in isolation. But with the advent of the Dark Shadows, which occurred soon after the end of the Great War Against Chaos in 2302 IC, they have been forced to take a more active role, guiding their most reliable allies in both the defense of Albion and the oppression of chaos marching to war with their fellow inhabitants of Albion.</p>\n<p>Druids are strange people, red haired, muscular individuals with spiraling blue tattoos and their mystical rods of command, inscribed with ogham signs. They are able and skilled magic users that try to protect the artefacts of the Old Ones. Sometimes they utilize the Giants to move some of the large and heavy Ogham Stones following their visions of fulfilling the great plan of the Old Ones.</p>\n<p>During the Dark Shadows, the Druids braved the perilous crossing over the Great Ocean to seek out noble civilizations. They foretold of great danger should their homeland of Albion fall; the forces that bind the Chaos mists to the northern realms would weaken and in so doing Daemon armies would be able to descend upon the world. To those who would help protect the isle they promised to teach secrets lost to civilization since the disappearance of the Old Ones. Fleets of adventurers and conquerors of all races set sail to the shores of Albion, while the mist and swirling fog around the island vanished, and the events of the Dark Shadows took place. In the end, the Druids and the Forces of Order won.</p>\n<p>In the aftermath of the events of the Dark Shadows, many of the surviving Druids followed their fallen brethren that fled from Albion to hunt and track them down. They have since travelled all around the Warhammer world and sold their services as Dogs of War to the local leaders of men. They live as hermits, preserving the sorceries of their ancient land through ritual and ceremony, waiting for the day when the mists will rise, and they can return home once more.</p>\n<p><strong>Species: </strong>Human (Albion)</p>\n<p><strong>Class: </strong>Academic</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Druid Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width:634px;height:32px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:16px;text-align:center\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;height:16px;text-align:center\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width:62px;height:16px;text-align:center\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width:62px;height:16px;text-align:center\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width:63px;height:16px;text-align:center\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:16px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;height:16px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"width:61px;height:16px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width:62px;height:16px;text-align:center\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width:62px;height:16px;text-align:center\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width:63px;height:16px;text-align:center\">III</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.V8BAK6mr3OA1Ml3t]{Druidic Apprentice}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.3MbQF1W8U18ba9fb]{Channelling ( Color)}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Herbs)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.9sMAf0xmehjEmUao]{Fast Hands}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.1dUizIgLBgn4jICC]{Strider (Woodlands)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Animal Hide Sack, Quarterstaff, Tribal Tattoos</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.C5CfeVeePehYSCnh]{Druid}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.jLyoyqwmBVPjRjhM]{Melee (Brawling)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Charms)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.9fq6p9Q6H02LjaSi]{Animal Affinity}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Beasts, Hedgecraft, Life or Light)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Animal Hide Cloak with Skull Headdress, Healing Draught, Trade Tools (Charms)</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.vK4eizeuwvCypQC8]{Druidic Master}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Dhar)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Spirits)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Nj3tC8A5fZ3zEdMR]{Holy Visions}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.wNvPXAhlKABl6hpk]{Pure Soul}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vMYEkrWj0ip6ZOdv]{Resistance (Corruption)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Isolated Hut</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.qdLCJu5p6QM8rUpa]{Truthsayer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Chaos)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GHmXS9zGNx3PWYZc]{Master Tradesman (Charms)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Spirits)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Ywo6fZNPC4zbHHSQ]{Strong-minded}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizar