rt, Riding Horse with Saddle and Tack, Shield, Trade Tools (Farrier)</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.RPDw1S2YjvklhalR]{Crusader}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.nqhgjUbJWglxU59j]{Language (Battle Tongue)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.d9bGxy6Y3u3rOHIN]{Lore (Theology)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.ZqYYWZuWwqMb3wVf]{Melee (Flail)}&nbsp;<em>or </em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Lst4xxUcxTYMlD3U]{Melee (Two-Handed)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bJBesrdCaDqaXbQg]{Melee (Parry)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.726gbrANZt8OqXr5]{Linguistics}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.uRvOg8AnCcP2ufx8]{Resolute}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IT3s7rmQFGNzIfYq]{Shieldsman}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Flail or Great Weapon, Large Shield, Melee Weapon (Any), Plate Armor and Helm</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.GUH2iJf3ut8acImK]{Knight Templar}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.oRx92ByVNEBN6YkK]{Berserk Charge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vMYEkrWj0ip6ZOdv]{Resistance (Corruption)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Barding, Quality Melee Weapon (Any), Religious Symbol</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.98bxPnwXo3PdU2Qr]{Knight Chaplain}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.9xR9uO8FIvi4YsJp]{Pray}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bVdhLdfuSAfMi3qq]{Secret Signs (Knightly Order)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.QyjWtSdnVMT04l5Y]{Bless (Any)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Nj3tC8A5fZ3zEdMR]{Holy Visions}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.wNvPXAhlKABl6hpk]{Pure Soul}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Foot Squire, Plumed Great Helm, Small Unit of Crusaders, Subordinate Priest <em>or </em>War Priest, Temple</p>","_id":"sABW6Ss6FWc4Pr4K"}
{"name":"Inquisidor","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.AhlSIqZO1L24RtwO"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Inquisidor</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;There are shadows in every corner, faces hiding truths that some would rather remain unburied. We have a duty to truth, to expose it, ugly as it may be, to render it into submission. Lies come In many a form, from the dejected corruption of an official to the taint of the dreaded mutation. And by Myrmidia&rsquo;s Grace and Wisdom, all who seek to sully her teachings will face our judgment. We are her Arms, her Eyes and her Ears. We are the true protectors against lack of belief.&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Laurenzo Taurquema, Gran Inquisidor</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Estalia is a region dominated by belief. It is well known that above the will of kings and their laws, Myrmidia&rsquo;s teachings hold sway for all that wish to live within the many Kingdoms, Baronies and Dukedoms. And to uphold these teachings, the Church of Myrmidia early on formed an organization capable of enforcing such power. La Inquisici&oacute;n was a body of devotees holding great sway in Estalia, ensuring the teachings of Myrmidia would come through all strata of society where possible.</p>\n<p>It gained significant power during the reconquering efforts, with Inquisitors joining the armed hosts of Estalia against the invading forces and acting by way of political officers. After the reconquering efforts started to refocus, so did the way the Inquisici&oacute;n sought to hold sway over society. The Inquisition Schools of Magritta were born out of this necessity, to form specialized members in order to tackle increasingly complicated issues both in Estalian interior and exterior politics. The major lingering threat of Skaven has been a constant issue to Estalia&rsquo;s people for centuries, and the efforts of the Inquisidors has been vital to stemming the tide of endless rat men. Many Skaven slaves, clan rats and stormvermin have met their end at the blade of these expert rat killers. Deus Myrmidia!</p>\n<p>From the fighting in the borders to the courtrooms; dealing with the influence of Chaos and diplomacy; these men became the middlemen for almost all aspects of Estalian society. It is stated that at one point, royally appointed judges got ousted by members of the Inquisition for giving out a contrarian verdict.</p>\n<p>The most famous of these Inquisidores goes by Laurenzo Taurquema, who some say controls the kings of Estalia like they&rsquo;re puppets in his grand schemes. And who can say? While not completely closed to the world, the workings of Estalian laws and doctrine are held close like a secret better left buried. And one can only imagine how these individuals, trained since birth and being taught all the ways the men can be broken, would react to a world broken in faith.</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Estalian)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Ranger</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Inquisidor Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.j9zSvJIGJl4U5vxi]{Initiate}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.nqhgjUbJWglxU59j]{Language (Battle Tongue)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Myrmidia)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Torture)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.4mJoPBw4drm1kv2D]{Melee (Fencing)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.IFKWu98qmWpaSfUi]{Ambidextrous}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Instruments of Torture, Bellona Myrmidia book</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.n9gJRagX5ArPd9oe]{Inquisidor}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Skavens)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}&nbsp;<em>or </em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bJBesrdCaDqaXbQg]{Melee (Parry)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.H2upcZ7q7qAPtPic]{Ranged (Blackpowder)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.5lcttqGToT54WFrl]{Marksman}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.XSb3QVB9ipPBFt56]{Shadow}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Feathered Hat, Leather Jack, Pair of Pistols, Riding Horse with Saddle and Tack, Rope, Silvered Rapier</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.H8X7jDnoL0gwDIZi]{Juramentado}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Estalia)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.5eDd6iFeR9G6cCfz]{Fast Shot}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Skavens)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.SgjJMBgc85aswvhm]{Relentless}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.x8jsChg17VQ9XgiK]{Riposte}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Subordinate Initiates, Quality Clothing, Quality Gun (Any), 10 Silver Bullets with Powder</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.mVDINpvjwA2SGhYn]{Evocador}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Arabyan)}&nbsp;<em>or </em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.12e3H6NX4JH0bwI3]{Language (Tilean)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Politics)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.wNvPXAhlKABl6hpk]{Pure Soul}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Best Quality Courtly Garb, Subordinate Inquisidores, Seal of Taurquema</p>","_id":"sIKylQr6t0SfjUIJ"}
{"_id":"sMcpz0qmPATlfkzy","name":"Almogavar","content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Almogavar</h1>\n<p>The Estalian common folk are accustomed to war. Ever since the evil Caliph Jaffar invaded their land, Estalian shepherds found few options for survival within the harsh mountains bordering Brettonia and Tilea. The easiest one became that which their forefathers had been forced to by the previous kings and nobles: That of raiding and pillaging. And soon after, there was not a single Estalian shepherd that had not grown up sullying his blade once. Estalian Almogavars (a term coined by the Arabyans, meaning &ldquo;Rioters&rdquo;) became an essential part of the reconquering efforts by the Estalian kingdoms, often employing these warbands as mobile light infantry to supplement their own rigid formations. These men came from all walks of life and joined a &ldquo;Compa&ntilde;ia&rdquo;, lead at first by charismatic or veteran individuals with tactical knowledge. These took part in battle by harassing the enemy position with well-placed javelin throws and forcing encounters with enemy infantry on uneven terrain. Outside of battle, their pillaging expertise put the tales of Tilean raiders to shame, destroying the ability for the Caliph to retain his stranglehold on the Peninsula. After these reconquering efforts began their decline, these men became mercenaries in a similar vein to those found in Tilean society, still serving the many remaining baronies, duchies and kingdoms within Estalia and fighting their battles. Their composition became much more professional, the &ldquo;Compa&ntilde;ias&rdquo; forming their own sense of identity and unity amongst themselves and in-between. The leaders of these groups, now known as &ldquo;Adalid&rdquo;, became lower noblemen within Estalian society, capable of fielding a military power that, while not threatening to major stability, could cause major damage. These mercenaries found themselves travelling far beyond the reaches of Estalia and Tilea, wandering over the northernmost icy forests of Kislev, the quibbles and disputes of the Border Princes, the silky sands of Araby and the fearsome jungles of the New World. While bound to their lieges and their kingdom first, these &ldquo;Compa&ntilde;ias&rdquo; value the survival of their companionship second&hellip; and the glint of gold and coin third. And, even though they may seem less illustrious and meritorious than their Tilean counterparts, it is wise to remember this old Estalian proverb:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;M&aacute;s has bien de reirte de nos, burlarte de nos y hartarte de nos&hellip; pero has bien de no enga&ntilde;ar a nos, o habr&aacute; de nos de quemar a ceniza la fortuna de vos&rdquo; (You&rsquo;d do well in laughing at us, mocking us and being fed up with us&hellip; but you&rsquo;d do well in not cheating us, or we will burn your fortunes to ash).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Estalian)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Almogavar Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0712%; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.53125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.28125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.28125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.28125%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.531