{"_id":"yXfHVYxVtACtjRo5","name":"Skald","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dENNHtHeskUDW25B"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Skald</h1>\n<blockquote>&ldquo;They came out of the North, bringing with them fire and ruin. Not since the Great War Against Chaos had the Empire seen so furious an invasion from the barbarian worshipers of the Dark Gods. Is this war a madman's quest for revenge, or is it the beginning of the end?&rdquo;<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Anonymous</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Skalds are the keepers of lore, the chroniclers of the histories of the Norse. Part entertainer, part warrior, these individuals are held in high esteem for their wisdom and knowledge. All Kings keep Skalds in their retinues, as do most Jarls. When the call for war is sounded, the Skald bears the banner and marches to battle with his comrades.</p>\n<p>The skald rises at an early hour, as soon as the breakfast fires in the Jarl&rsquo;s great hall are kindled. After all, he would be grieved to miss any pertinent gossip (and heartbroken to miss impertinent gossip). Also, the skald may have enemies (at least, he will if he&rsquo;s any good) and in Norsca it is wise to wake before those who hate you. A skald is a learned man, contemplating the written sagas of the Norse and talking to his elders about their recollections. He may also be a musician and, if so, will spend time practicing his craft. The skald has his ears open for news of recent events, and his eyes on any behavioral quirks of members of the jarl&rsquo;s court. The skald performs one function above all others&mdash;offering entertaining and irreverent commentary on current affairs.</p>\n<p>When the night draws in the jarl may preside over a feast and call the skald to perform. The skald sings the sagas of the Norsemen and plays sweet music. As mead flows the Northmen call for more ribald entertainment and the skald employs his skills as a mimic and comedian, mocking those in attendance, and even parodying the jarl himself.</p>\n<p>The skald treads a fine line. If he&rsquo;s careful, he will be heaped with praise and fame, and even given the honor of bearing the Jarl&rsquo;s banner in times of war. Most Northmen pride themselves on being able to take a good joke, so the Skald is confident that his targets will probably take it in good humor. However, if he takes his act too far, he may find himself hewn apart by an offended reaver.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Human (Norscan)</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Ranger</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Skald Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 69px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 61px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"width: 62px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 63px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.CBVFiCBi6icPg2Re]{Marked Poet}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HO8vIjGTHjmenIaV]{Perform (Any)}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bBLK2hznjPlby6Jb]{Play (Harp)} or @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bBLK2hznjPlby6Jb]{Play (Lyre)}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rvd0S8Z0v2m0MHmD]{Sleight of Hand}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.LU6Ycl5z4kp1Wr04]{Mimic}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.XU7D9CCmumuhqDUi]{Public Speaker}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Instrument, Tribe Tattoos</p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.1zJoAqodqFbe8n6O]{Skald}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.fdq3RFSOKl5b3WzW]{Art ( Poetry)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.UFunAopCNaD8Zdc7]{Entertain (Singing)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.1SVd48nGAHbASqr8]{Entertain (Comedy)}&nbsp;<em>or </em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Speeches)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Norsca)}, @Compendiu